full_text: Screened by NARA, 6/13/2023 Department of Homeland Security OMB No 1615-0054; Expires 06/30/07 U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services Form N-445, Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony A# A043194558 WSC*001669594 Date August 28, 2007 APPLICANT COPY JULIO CESAR ZEPEDA FUENTES FOIA (b)(6) You are hereby notified to appear for a Naturalization Oath Ceremony on: Friday, September 14 2007 at: US DISTRICT COURT CENTRAL DISTRICT 1201 SOUTH FIGUEROA STREET LOS ANGELES, CA 90012 LOS ANGELES CONVENTION CENTER, HALL, GATE NONE Please report promptly at 8:00 AM You must bring the following with you: This letter, WITH ALL THE QUESTIONS ON PAGE 2 ANSWERED. TYPE OR PRINT ANSWERS IN X BLACK INK. Permanent Resident Card. Reentry Permit or Refugee Travel Document. Any Immigration documents you may have. If the naturalization application is on behalf of your child (children), bring your child (children). Other. Proper attire should be worn. If you cannot come to this ceremony, return this notice immediately and state why you cannot appear. In such case, you will be sent another notice of ceremony at a later date. You must appear at an oath ceremony to complete the naturalization process. Form N-445 (Rev. 07/29/05)N
